    <note>Tao(1) Tuan [21548] The jinshi lists in local histories have different mingzi for both Tuan and his son, Pang [21549] (q.v.), than does Wang(1) Zao [11625] in his funerary inscription for Pang. Wuxing zhi, 17.12a and Zhejiang TZ, 124.2b (derived from Wuxing zhi) have Dui for Tuan (and Zhao for Pang). Although it is probably more likely that the SBCK edition of Wang(1) Zao's wenji has copying errors than the local histories, I will use the former--these were the only Tao jinshi from Huzhou. Pang is identified as a Wuxing person and was buried in Wucheng (modern Wuxing), but, here, I follow the Zhejiang TZ, which identifies both Dui(Tuan) and Pang(Zhao) as Guian residents.</note>
